result.name: Chi Chi Cham - 吱吱朕

reviews.text: The food was very tasty and delicious. Prices are acceptable and the service was great. The only comment I’d have is that it’s quite noisy inside so it was difficult to hear our companions. Otherwise, it’s a fun place and I suppose the noise adds to the hip ambiance.

Great happy hour prices.
Very good service.
Food prices a little pricy, but great drinks make up for it.
Only thing is i wont touch their draft beers, see pic!

Chi Chi Cham .ust be the best happy hour in HKG!! Get your fill of wisely priced sake, wine, and Asahi here. I never had a bite to eat, but had major food envy for every dish around me. Just visiting Hong Kong, and I've been here two nights in a row. 🤭
Cute bar, nice staff, good sashimi and drinks
Really good Japanese fusion with really good interior. Staff were attentive! Generous serving as well!
